In this article, President Trump discusses the state of the country's finances and his plans for the budget. He congratulates Mick Mulvaney on his confirmation as director and expresses confidence in his ability to manage the budget. The President acknowledges that the budget is in a mess, with the national debt having doubled in the last eight years. He emphasizes that the budget will reflect the priorities of the American people and vows to protect every last American and tax dollar. The President highlights the need to make the government leaner and more accountable, reduce improper payments, negotiate better prices, and find savings. He mentions the hiring freeze on nonessential government workers and appointing a Cabinet that can manage dollars wisely. The President also mentions the importance of taking care of the military and healthcare, which is being finalized before the tax plan can be submitted.